Install the jenkins
*****************************************
>step1 :installing the services 
     yum install tar make wget make fontconfig java-21-openjdk-devel git vim unzip -y

>step2 :vim :vim is a editor it is create,edit and modifying the file 
       open the file "vim jenkins-setup.sh"

>step3 :go to the browser in search bar 'jenkins downlaod' enter the website to take the key and small changes the key
      
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
    https://pkg.jenkins.io/rpm-stable/jenkins.repo
sudo yum upgrade -y
# Add required dependencies for the jenkins package
sudo yum install fontconfig java-21-openjdk -y
sudo yum install jenkins -y
sudo systemctl daemon-reload	

>step 4:give the file permissions 
       chmod +x jenkins-setup.sh

>step 5:give the path location
       ./jenkins-setup

>step 6:after installing the jenkins check the status
        systemctl status jenkins
     if the service is dead 
        systemctl start jenkins
     and enable the jenkins service 
        systemctl enable jenkins 
     then check the status 
       systemctl status jenkins

>step 6:Host confuriguation with the jenkins ip address
      firewall-cmd --reload
      firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=8080/tcp

>step 7:goto the browser open the jenkins with the ip address

        example: 192.168.106.144:8080

>step 8:in cli take the jenkins password 
       cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword.

>step 9:click the continue

>step 10:click the 'installing suggested plugins'

>step 11:after installing give the cridentials
      example: username
               password
               confirm password
               full name 
               e-mail
            click the continue   
>stap 12:then jenkins setup is ready



